November 12, 2008 on ABC News



Former evangelical leader Ted Haggard broke his silence on a sex scandal that ended

his career during a sermon at a small church in Illinois. 

Haggard said that his sins stemmed from sexual abuse that received in the second 

grade. 

Haggard was one of the most powerful evangelical leaders in the country when 

accusations of gay sex and drug use caused him to step down.

